  "title": "priceRanges entered as floats being truncated to integers",
  "body": "\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nBug\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nIn instantsearch.js 1.11.7, the priceRanges and priceRange widgets truncate manually entered values to integers.  This makes it hard to search for small values in ranges like 0.00 to 0.50.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\ninstantsearch.js accepts manually entered numbers as integers or floats.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\n\r\nAll.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the proposed solution?**\r\n\r\nI don't have a patch or test case for you.  You can use the instantsearch.js example on this page to see the problem:\r\n\r\nhttps://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v1/documentation/#priceranges\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n\r\n1.11.7\r\n",
